Interface CheckRelation<C,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - Type representing the keys.
    T - Type representing the values.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CheckSubdomainRelation, ImplementationCheckRelation, SubdomainDomainRelation

    public interface CheckRelation<C,T>
    An interface defining basic methods for a relation in use in this plugin.

    Jack Coffey

    • Method Detail

      • find

        T find​(C key)
        C type keys and T type values are relationallly linked to eachother. By providing a key, it is possible to retrive a value.
        Parameters:
        key - A key relationally linked to a T type value.
        Returns:
        A value linked to the provided key.

      • search

        C[] search​(T value)
        C type keys and T type values are relationallly linked to eachother. By providing a value, it is possible to retrieve an array of keys.
        Parameters:
        value - A T type value.
        Returns:
        An Array of C type objects relationally linked to the provided T type value.
